# Keep Documentation Updated

When any feature is added, changed, or removed, update the relevant documentation:

## Always check these files

- **`README.md`** — update if the change affects: architecture diagram, project structure, config examples, API endpoints, CLI commands, prerequisites, roadmap items
- **`CONTRIBUTING.md`** — update if the change affects: setup steps, code standards, project layout, how to add backends/tools/pages
- **`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`** — update if the change affects: system architecture, extension model, ReAct loop, UI layout, framework comparisons, change map table
- **`docs/guide/extending-klaus.md`** — update if adding a new extension point, superpower example, or developer workflow

## Feature-specific docs

| Change type | Update these docs |
|-------------|-------------------|
| New superpower or tool | `docs/guide/adding-tools.md`, `docs/guide/extending-klaus.md` |
| New MD agent | `docs/guide/orchestration.md` |
| New model backend | `docs/guide/adding-backends.md` |
| New API endpoint | `docs/reference/api.md` |
| New SSE event | `docs/reference/sse.md` |
| Config changes | `docs/reference/configuration.md` |
| UI changes | `docs/guide/ui-guide.md` |
| Database changes | `docs/reference/database.md` |
| Memory system changes | `docs/guide/memory-system.md` |
| Orchestrator changes | `docs/guide/orchestration.md` |

## Rules

- Include both the **simple approach** (MD file) and the **full approach** (Python class) when documenting extension points
- Show working code examples, not pseudocode
- Keep the architecture diagram in `ARCHITECTURE.md` and `README.md` in sync
- Update the project structure tree in `README.md` when files/directories are added
- Update the VitePress sidebar in `docs/.vitepress/config.mts` when adding new doc pages
- Do NOT update docs for internal refactors, test-only changes, or lint fixes
